Image supplied: Wouter Kellerman performing at the Dubai Expo Over the course of nine albums, Kellerman has steadfastly built on his classical training, to create a signature sound that’s earned him praise and numerous awards.Winds of Samsara, a collaboration with Indian composer and producer Ricky Kej, was named winner in the Best New Age Album category at the 57th Annual Grammy® Awards in 2015. In less than a month, Wouter and David Arkenstone will find out if they the recipients of another Grammy Award for the album Pangaea. The award will be hosted by Trevor Noah on 3 April 2022.The album is themed around Pangaea, which is the name of the supercontinent that existed before it broke apart to form the existing continents. The music calls for unity in these divided times and for a culture of nurturing the earth and nature.I caught up with Wouter last week….bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} The new decade means…Exciting opportunities..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Fame is about…Generally, fame is not desirable, in many cases leading to loss of privacy and illusions of grandeur – luckily I have no chance to become famous, being a flutist..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Retirement will happen when…Not anytime soon, I am loving working..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} I don't do…Hate.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What does music mean to you?Travelling on a shared road of passion and love..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} My music is about…Expressing passion and love. .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} I would love to co-write with… Norah Jones.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Where do you go for inspiration to create?I listen to beautiful music or jam with people who make beautiful sounds..bizicon + br{display:none} h2